article.headline: UCLA 82, Oregon 63
article.story:
LOS ANGELES (AP) -- Noelle Quinn scored 16 points and Nikki Blue
had 15 as UCLA beat Oregon 82-63 Tuesday night.

Quinn went 7-for-14 from the field and Blue went 6-for-8,
leading the Bruins (5-4) to a 51.5 percent performance from the
floor.

Oregon (8-2) had a seven-game winning streak snapped.

Carolyn Ganes led the Ducks with 15 points on 7-for 10 shooting.
Chelsea Wagner had 11 points, and Cicely Oaks and Gabrielle
Richards had 10 apiece.

Lindsay Pluimer and Chinyere Ibekwe added 12 points apiece for
UCLA. Pluimer also had eight rebounds to lead the Bruins.
